1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Welcome. This tutorial covers the daily RP Rental workflow now migrated from manual steps into Odoo.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Odoo is the source of truth for customers, equipment, availability, contracts, deliveries, returns, quality checks, and billing.

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:26,000
If it is not in Odoo, it did not happen. Keep every step updated as you work.

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Start from the main Apps menu. Use the global search bar to quickly find Customers, Rentals, and Products.

5
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Your role controls what you can do. If a button is missing, request access instead of working around the process.

6
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Before creating a quote, confirm the customer exists and the billing and delivery contacts are correct.

7
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Create new customers only when needed. Add phone, email, addresses, and set any payment terms required by the business.

8
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Rental products represent what you sell. Rental assets represent the physical units that get delivered and returned.

9
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Use the imported catalog and product codes to search quickly. Confirm the item is marked as rentable and available.

10
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Always confirm availability for the requested dates before promising equipment to the customer.

11
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Create a new quotation for the customer, then add the rental products and set the rental start and end dates.

12
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Set the rental period before validating pricing. Dates drive availability and the correct rental price calculation.

13
00:01:52,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Pricing follows the imported rate matrix. Confirm daily, weekly, and monthly cycles align with the agreed commercial terms.

14
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:13,000
When the customer approves, confirm the quotation. This becomes the rental contract and triggers the operational workflow.

15
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Review the delivery order, ensure the correct warehouse and destination, and prepare assets for dispatch.

16
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Validate the delivery in Odoo when the equipment leaves. Record any required evidence and confirm the on-site location.

17
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:42,000
If dates or quantities change, update the contract immediately. Do not track changes only in chat or email.

18
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:51,000
If an asset is replaced, record the exchange so traceability and billing remain correct.

19
00:02:51,000 --> 00:03:00,000
For partial returns, process the return picking and adjust the contract lines so invoicing stays accurate.

20
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:09,000
When all equipment returns, validate the return picking. This is the handoff into quality control.

21
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Run the Rental Return inspection. Capture condition notes and issues so maintenance and billing decisions are supported.

22
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Before sending equipment out again, complete the Ready-To-Rent inspection. This prevents avoidable failures in the field.

23
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Billing is driven by the contract and time. Generate invoices based on the agreed billing cadence.

24
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:52,000
If your process uses the 3-3-3 rule, apply it consistently: daily, weekly, and monthly billing logic must match the contract.

25
00:03:52,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Create the invoice from the rental order, review line items and taxes, then send it to the customer from Odoo.

26
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:12,000
When payment is received, register it and reconcile. Keep Accounting accurate so reporting stays reliable.

27
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Use reports to monitor open rentals, asset utilization, overdue returns, invoices due, and quality backlog.

28
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Once the rental is fully returned, quality is completed, and invoicing is done, close the loop and archive evidence.

29
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:39,000
You are ready to run the daily workflow in Odoo using your real catalog, assets, and rates.

